<subSubSection pageId="97" pageNumber="98" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="97.[151,1436,158,351]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,158,184]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body fusiform; gnathosoma large, abruptly curved and bent down near base; scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[161,185,200,225]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">sc</emphasis>
) and tubercles ahead of rear shield margin; genual II seta absent, empodium divided; coxae I and coxae II each with 3 setae; opisthosoma with a furrow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="97.[151,1436,158,351]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">
This genus consists of 2 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[637,885,283,309]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[743,801,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Only one species has been recorded from Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
